<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 3:02PM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
McIntosh and northwestern Pittsburg Counties through 345 PM CST...
At 302 PM CST, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
west of Scipio, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Crowder...                        Indianola...
Hanna...                          Scipio...
Vernon...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
